               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the owner in some of the supplication formulas; headings or incipits of the constituent texts; directives for the ministers; most of the abbreviations; part of the musical notation signs above the lines; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numbers.&#xD;
&#xD;
Incipits of some of the texts (e. g., fols. 1ra-rb, 106vb) are written alternately in red and black lines.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Hand a is unstable, on some folios even and uneven lines alternate, the letters are generally slanting to the right. Hand b is characterized by more upright letters.</note>
                     <note>Fols.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES176177">176-177</ref>(quire XXIII) are smaller in size than the rest of the folios.</note>
                     <note>Text V: Incipit (?): እሰግድ፡ ለኪ፡ ኦእግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ ድንግል፡ በከመ፡ ወደሰኪ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈ፡ ወርቅ፡ በድርሳኑ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፨ Explicit: ኦእግዝእትየ፡ ማ፡ ጸልይ፡ ወሰአሊ፡ ሐበ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልድኪ፡ ከመ፡ ይስረይ፡ ለነ፡ ኃጠውኢነ፨</note>
                  </msItem>
