                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#7vb">Fol. 7vb</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 7vb: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ኢየሱ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለወልዱ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡ ወለእሙ፡  ወለተ፡ ማርያም።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"> Fol. 7vb: This book belongs to Wäldä ʾIyäsu(s) who has given it to his son ʾAtnatewos and to his mother Wälättä Maryam.</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#23v">Fol. 23v</locus>: Note on grain donations to the church.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic. The note mentions ras Wäldä Śǝllase.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3"> <locus target="#25vb">Fol. 25vb</locus>: Note on grain donations to the church.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic. Incomplete. The note mentions ras Wäräňňa and nǝguś Yoḥannǝs.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4"> <locus target="#172vb">Fol. 172vb</locus>: Supplication for the owner of the Ms. and for his relatives.<q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 172vb: በረከቶሙ፡ ለአበዊነ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሮሙ፡ ወልደ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ወለወልዱ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡ ወለእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም። ዘአንበብክዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡መጽሐፍ፡ ኢትርስኡነ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"> Fol. 172vb: May the blessing of our fathers the Apostles be with their beloved Wäldä ʾIyäsus, and with his son ʾAtnatewos, and with his mother Wälättä Maryam. You who read this book, do not forget us; (recite for us) the Paternoster.</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Two apparently recent marginal notes: ዘደብረ ጽዮን ቅድስት ማርያም መጽሓፈ ቅዳሴ and ደብረ ጽዮን ቅድስት ማርያም ቤተ ክርስቲያን ዘብሄረ ነቢያት።: fol. 1r.&#xD;
- Crude drawings of crosses in the margins: fols. 17r, 28v, 40r, 69r, 87r, 88r,&#xD;
- Notes (mostly crude) in the upper margin: fols. 17v, 33v, 43v, 46r, 46v, etc.&#xD;
C- rude notes in the right-hand margin (writing exercise): fol. 101r.&#xD;
- Pieces of parchment possibly originating from different Mss., sewn onto the leaves, with text: fols. 38v, 43r.&#xD;
- Ms. of smaller size sewn on to the leaf. The Ms. consists of 3 folios and contains prayers from the Ordinary of the Mass: fol. 64r.&#xD;
- Parchment stripe sewn on to the leaf: fol. 43v.&#xD;
- Part of the Anaphora of St. Epiphanius, crudely written in brown ink: fols. 151r, in the upper margin, 151va-vb, 152r, in the upper and right-hand margins.&#xD;
- Arithmetical calculation (1984 – 996 = 988) written in European digits: fol. 176vb.</item>
